## Question

I am using a lazy-loaded tree.

When loading the child-items, the returned can already contain their own children. E.g. in the following example, clicking on `Switzerland` would return the following sub-tree.

```json
[{
  "id": "canton-zh",
  "label": "Canton of Zurich",
  "children": [{
    "id": "city-zh",
    "label": "Zürich",
    "children": [{
      "id": "office-zh",
      "label": "Office Zurich"
    }]
  }]
}]
```

I don't find a way to automatically open all sub-items.

## Motivation

If the sub-tree is nested and only contains a couple of items or sub-items, we don't want the users to have to click their way to the items.

## What I tired

1. I tried it just doing nothing, and hoping for the best.
2. I tried hacking my way there by making the `expandedItems` controlled.
3. I tried hacking my way there by using the `apiRef`.

